I agree with Ryan C on this one.
New Asian Kitchen is the best small and independent fast food Chinese of it's kind in the area.
Nobody in a several mile radius makes Chinese Food as tasty.
Food packed with lots of fresh vegetables and great flavors.
They even make the very hard to make Cantonese Dry Sauteed Beef Chow Fun that's considered a major test for Cantonese Chefs for cooking and their version is very good indeed and you will not see that dish at most places I note.
My personal favorites are the Szechuan Chicken, the  Curry Chicken and the Yui Shan Eggplant.
Lately they don't make these dishes as spicy as they use to make them but they are so flavorful it doesn't matter.
The people that own the place are very nice and they will make anything within reason for you.
I have at least a half dozen places that are closer that aren't nearly as good.
This place isn't fancy  at all but it seems clean and is very reasonably priced.

